==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Joint-fir
<hw>Joint"-fir`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus (<gen>Ephedra</gen>) of leafless shrubs, with the stems
conspicuously jointed; -- called also <altname>shrubby
horsetail</altname>. There are about thirty species, of which two or
three are found from Texas to California.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jointing</ent>⟦br⟧
